{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2017-09-25--Configuring-and-using-vim/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Joel's dev blog","author":"Joel Mun","siteUrl":"https://9oelm.github.io"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"cf27958d-7828-57d6-8690-6174121bdc97","excerpt":"This looks like a pretty awesome boilerplate! Well, I just looked at this repository and it just looks amazing. I cloned the repo to my local computer and…","html":"<h2 id=\"this-looks-like-a-pretty-awesome-boilerplate\" style=\"position:relative;\">This looks like a pretty awesome boilerplate!<a href=\"#this-looks-like-a-pretty-awesome-boilerplate\" aria-label=\"this looks like a pretty awesome boilerplate permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Well, I just looked at <a href=\"https://github.com/amix/vimrc\">this repository</a> and it just looks amazing.</p>\n<p>I cloned the repo to my local computer and installed the configuration.</p>\n<h2 id=\"vim-configuration-information\" style=\"position:relative;\">Vim configuration information<a href=\"#vim-configuration-information\" aria-label=\"vim configuration information permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>For your information, the vim configurations are stored in <code class=\"language-text\">~/.vimrc</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">~/.vim_runtime</code> (if you installed the configurations from that repository).</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">~/.viminfo</code> acts as a cache/history for vim.</p>\n<h2 id=\"advanced-configurations\" style=\"position:relative;\">Advanced configurations<a href=\"#advanced-configurations\" aria-label=\"advanced configurations permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"note\" style=\"position:relative;\">Note<a href=\"#note\" aria-label=\"note permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Use <code class=\"language-text\">my_configs.vim</code> if you are using <code class=\"language-text\">amix/vimrc</code> repo.</p>\n<h3 id=\"color-scheme\" style=\"position:relative;\">Color scheme<a href=\"#color-scheme\" aria-label=\"color scheme permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Add to vim configuations file (for me, <code class=\"language-text\">my_configs.vim</code>) these lines:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">syntax enable\nset background=dark\ncolorscheme solarized</code></pre></div>\n<p>and da-da, the color scheme has changed (make sure you have solarized colorscheme installed beforehand)</p>\n<h3 id=\"using-plugins\" style=\"position:relative;\">Using plugins<a href=\"#using-plugins\" aria-label=\"using plugins permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>The installation shell script from the repository will install most of the plugins, so you just have to use them.</p>\n<p>For example, you could use <a href=\"https://github.com/scrooloose/nerdtree\">NERDTree</a> by typing <code class=\"language-text\">ESC + : + NERDTreeToggle</code>.</p>\n<p>Use other plugins in the same way. For example, use <a href=\"https://github.com/vim-scripts/mru.vim\">MRU.vim</a> to see recently opened files:\n<code class=\"language-text\">ESC + : + MRU</code> will show you recently opened files.</p>\n<h3 id=\"tab-space\" style=\"position:relative;\">Tab space<a href=\"#tab-space\" aria-label=\"tab space permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>The source file has the size of <code class=\"language-text\">2 spaces</code> for a <code class=\"language-text\">tab</code> but vim is currently configured to use the size of <code class=\"language-text\">4 spaces</code> for a <code class=\"language-text\">tab</code>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"1-how-to-beautify-the-file\" style=\"position:relative;\">1. How to beautify the file<a href=\"#1-how-to-beautify-the-file\" aria-label=\"1 how to beautify the file permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h4>\n<p>Download the folder from <a href=\"https://github.com/Chiel92/vim-autoformat\">this repo</a> and put that into <code class=\"language-text\">sources_non_forked</code> folder if you have installed vim configurations from <a href=\"https://github.com/amix/vimrc\">the ultimate vim configuration repository</a>. Then it’s going to automatically work once you restart vim. Type <code class=\"language-text\">:Autoformat</code> to use.</p>\n<p><img src=\"%7B%7Bsite.url%7D%7D/assets/images/Vim/2vimBeautify.png\" alt=\"Autoformat\"></p>\n<h4 id=\"2-how-to-permanently-change-the-tab-size-to-2-spaces\" style=\"position:relative;\">2. How to permanently change the tab size to ‘2 spaces’<a href=\"#2-how-to-permanently-change-the-tab-size-to-2-spaces\" aria-label=\"2 how to permanently change the tab size to 2 spaces permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h4>\n<p>in <code class=\"language-text\">.vimrc</code>, paste the following:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">set tabstop=2 \" The 'size', the with of a tab is set to 2\nset shiftwidth=2 \" Indents will have width of 2\nset softtabstop=2 \" The number of columns for a tab is set to 2</code></pre></div>\n<p>consult the <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1878974/redefine-tab-as-4-spaces\">stackoverflow question</a> for more detail.</p>\n<h3 id=\"how-to-autoclose-html-tag\" style=\"position:relative;\">How to autoclose html tag<a href=\"#how-to-autoclose-html-tag\" aria-label=\"how to autoclose html tag permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Download <a href=\"https://github.com/alvan/vim-closetag\">the plugin from the repo</a>.</li>\n<li>Put that downloaded repo into <code class=\"language-text\">~/.vim/</code> or any designated folder.</li>\n<li>If you are using pathogen, closetag.vim will start automatically working. For additional configurations, see the repo.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"how-to-autocomplete-braces\" style=\"position:relative;\">How to autocomplete braces<a href=\"#how-to-autocomplete-braces\" aria-label=\"how to autocomplete braces permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Download <a href=\"https://github.com/jiangmiao/auto-pairs\">the plugin</a>:</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">git clone git://github.com/jiangmiao/auto-pairs.git</code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Put it into the right folder (see how we did previous configs).</li>\n<li>Then it starts working once you restart vim.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-search-in-vim\" style=\"position:relative;\">How to search in vim<a href=\"#how-to-search-in-vim\" aria-label=\"how to search in vim permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Search command</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">ESC + : + / + [search pattern] + enter</code></pre></div>\n<p>Next match</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">n + enter</code></pre></div>\n<p>Previous match</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">N + enter</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-navigate-in-vim\" style=\"position:relative;\">How to navigate in vim<a href=\"#how-to-navigate-in-vim\" aria-label=\"how to navigate in vim permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Go forward by word</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">w</code></pre></div>\n<p>Go back by word</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">b</code></pre></div>\n<p>Move one character left</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">h</code></pre></div>\n<p>Move one character right</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">l</code></pre></div>\n<p>Move one row down</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">j</code></pre></div>\n<p>Move one row up</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">k</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-select-copy-and-paste-in-vim\" style=\"position:relative;\">How to select, copy and paste in vim<a href=\"#how-to-select-copy-and-paste-in-vim\" aria-label=\"how to select copy and paste in vim permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Select a line (up/down arrow key to include more/less lines)</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">V</code></pre></div>\n<p>Select texts (letter by letter)</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">v   </code></pre></div>\n<p>Select blocks</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">ctrl + v</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then\nDelete</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">d</code></pre></div>\n<p>Copy (called ‘yanking’)</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">y</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then\nPaste after cursor</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">p</code></pre></div>\n<p>Paste before cursor</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">P</code></pre></div>\n<p>Note: there is no default cutting operation that could be done with one command.</p>\n<h2 id=\"lines\" style=\"position:relative;\">Lines<a href=\"#lines\" aria-label=\"lines permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>open a line below the cursor and start insert mode</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">o</code></pre></div>\n<p>open a line above the cursor</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">O</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-undo\" style=\"position:relative;\">How to undo<a href=\"#how-to-undo\" aria-label=\"how to undo permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">u</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"opening-new-tabs\" style=\"position:relative;\">Opening new tabs<a href=\"#opening-new-tabs\" aria-label=\"opening new tabs permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">ESC + : + tabnew</code></pre></div>\n<p>To open a new tab,\nand</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">ESC + : + saveas [filename]</code></pre></div>\n<p>to save the file.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Configuring and using vim","date":"September 25, 2017","keywords":null},"fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"4 min read"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2017-09-25--Configuring-and-using-vim/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2017-09-23--Editing-environment-path-and-adding-custom-scripts/","readingTime":{"text":"2 min read"}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Editing environment path and adding custom scripts","tab":"post","tags":["linux","env"],"keywords":null}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2017-09-25--Turning-monitor-mode-on-and-off/","readingTime":{"text":"1 min read"}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Turning monitor mode on and off","tab":"post","tags":["hacking","monitor-mode","kali"],"keywords":null}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3128451518","426816048"]}